Good morning sir,

My project is titled "Machine Learning-Based Compiler Error Classification".

The objective of this project is to classify compiler error messages into lexical, syntactic, and semantic categories using machine learning techniques.

In this project, I first collected and preprocessed a dataset of compiler error messages.

Then I applied TF-IDF vectorization to convert text into numerical features.

After that, I trained multiple machine learning models including Logistic Regression, Random Forest, SVM, Gradient Boosting, and MLP.

I evaluated all models and selected the best-performing model based on accuracy.

To make the system user-friendly, I developed a Flask-based web application where users can input an error message and get instant classification.

This system helps developers understand errors quickly and also has security relevance since semantic errors can indicate vulnerabilities.

Now I will demonstrate the working of the system.